        <name>7.4.5.1 Exercise: Inverse of a 2 x 2 matrix (NOT IN QUIZ)</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Find the inverses of the following matrices&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(\bf A={@A@}\), \(\bf B={@B@}\), \(\bf C={@C@}\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;\(\bf A^{-1}=\) [[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;\(\bf B^{-1}=\) [[input:ans2]][[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;\(\bf C^{-1}=\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;FEEDBACK&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;The inverse of a 2 \(\times\) 2 matrix \[{@matrixabcd@}\] is \[\frac{1}{ad-bc}{@matrixdbca@}.\]&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Therefore the inverse of matrix \[\bf A = {@A@}\] is&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[\bf A^{-1} = \frac{1}{({@A[1,1]@}).({@A[2,2]@}) -({@A[1,2]@}).({@A[2,1]@})}{@ta1@} = \frac{1}{({@A[1,1]*A[2,2]@}) -({@A[1,2]*A[2,1]@})}{@ta1@} ={@ta1@}.\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The inverse of matrices \( \bf B\) and \( \bf C\) can be found similarly and are&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[ B^{-1} = {@ta2@} \quad C^{-1} = {@ta3@}.\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
